posts.name: James Spruill
posts.cooked:
Hello,

Good afternoon. My name is Dr. Spruill and I am the Coach of Team 9205 at American International Academy in Inkster, Michigan. I have been trying to purchase some swerve motors from Andy Mark and Swerve Specialists who have confirmed they are out of stock and will not have any until Fall 2023.

At this point, I am willing to use the MK4 modules so my team can get experience with these motors. If anyone is willing to part with their older MK4 modules please contact me.

posts.name: Chris Bale
posts.cooked: Just to clarify, are you looking for Swerve modules or the motors they use? Your post seems to use these terms interchangeably so it might be confusing to some.

posts.name: Patrick Woolfenden
posts.cooked:
AndyMark appears to have SDS MK4 modules in stock with the L1 or L2 gear ratio.

SDS is accepting orders on all modules, but with a lead time. Once we receive our latest batch of gears we will be able to send out many modules. Our lead time will be getting shorter through out the summer. We have increased production for the summer and are significantly out pacing demand at the moment. Our goal for this fall is to have the backlog cleared with modules on the shelf ready to ship.

posts.name: James Spruill
posts.cooked: I am looking for both the modules and the motors.

posts.name: James Spruill
posts.cooked: I checked with Andy Mark and those modules are on back order until fall 2023.

posts.name: Patrick Woolfenden
posts.cooked: You are able to add them to your cart if you do not have the motors included.

posts.name: Chris Bale
posts.cooked:
J.spruill:

I am looking for both the modules and the motors.

These appear to be in-stock: MK4 Module - L1 Reduction (NEO Version) - No Motors MK4 Module - L1 Reduction (Falcon Version) - No Motors MK4 Module - L2 Reduction (NEO Version) - No Motors MK4 Module - L2 Reduction (Falcon Version) - No Motors

The motors you’ll have to get separately at this point, either from a team, or wait for them to come in-stock. In general, I would expect the NEO motors to come back in-stock first (though there was a post the other day claiming, albeit without evidence, that Falcons will be back in September)
